downloadDescription: Carl and Richard talk feed synchronization with Steven Lees from Microsoft about FeedSync, a Windows Live Dev service for synchronizing RSS and Atom feeds, and FeedSync feeds across the web.
detailsSection: Steven Lees has worked on languages and developer tools at Microsoft for well over a decade. He’s currently a Principal Program Manager on the CSA Concept Development Team at Microsoft, working on web collaboration technology including FeedSync (http://feedsync.org) and Live Clipboard.
systemRequirementsSection: Presentations are played using the Microsoft Windows Media Player.
installInstructionSection:
- Select "Save this Program to Disk" to copy the download to your machine for installation at a later time.
- Once the file has been downloaded, execute it in order to extract the media file.
